Once you defeat Hardy, a hiker will show up near the circus entrance in one of the houses of Argate City. Talk to him and he'll move to Route 4. Rain - Long Sidequest. If the weather is rainy, we can get a Squirtle now. From the western entrance of the Byxbysion Wasteland, enter the first big building with all the stairs. There will be a person near the top, if its raining. Keep talking to him until he starts repeating his last dialog.

 

Exit out the northern entrance of the building and make your way east. If you changed all the big containers to red from blue, then a door will be open on the left (previously just the right building was open). Enter the left building. Keep making your way west, until you are outside again.

 

Slide down the ramps and enter the western opening. Keep heading east, until you are outside again. Jump off the ledge and enter the northern opening. Enter the hidden passage behind the western container. Keep making your way west and you will be outside again.

 

Slide down the ramp and enter the northern opening. Go up the ladder, then go back down the same ladder you just came up. Use Strength and push the 2 western boulders out of your way. Exit out the northern opening.

 

Change your weather to clear in this outside area. Squirtle will be in the small pool of water south of you.

In the back alley on the way to the Sanctum where you rescue Luna, head right. There is a rock you can mine. Mine it once and then use Blasting Powder to mine it again. Interact with the rock behind it and you will get a "Rare Candy". Go back to 7th st and it will get stolen. Go to the southwest sectino of 7th st and talk to the man below the girl in the caged area. He'll give it back to you. Go back to the northeast section of 7th st and enter the top most right room. Talk one of the men in that room, give him the "Rare Candy" and he'll give you Piplup.

column4: Follow the path until you can go down and collect a Rage Powder. Backtrack the way that you came from and all the way back to the Celestinine Cascade where you last saw Titania and Amaria. You should still have the Rage Powder at this point, since you used Surf instead of jumping across the rocks to get here. Use it on the nearby Crustle to wake him up. If it doesn't let you interact with it, you either don't have the Rage Powder, or you ran into a bug here. To fix it, enter the house/gym north of you and come back here. The Crustle should let you interact with it by using the Rage Powder. Enter the cave after the Crustle is gone. Inside, you can catch a Salandit. Make sure its a female if you want to evolve it.

Enter south through Surf, go west to get to an ice puzzle. Push the boulder west, go back up the waterfall and head southwest to go across a new path. Path splits east and west, go East. Go into the hidden entrance, and it'll be at the end of the path.

Go back down the waterfall, then west across the ice puzzle. Push the boulder west, go back up the waterfall and head southwest to go across the new path you made. Dive and find a hidden entrance at the end of the path. Keep following the path and when it splits east and west, go west. There is another hidden entrance in the same room. Next room has a hidden entrance in southwest corner. Lapras can be found here on Fridays.
